==<span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 22px">Overview</span>==
The '''Anchorian Geological Crisis''' was a seismic tectonic shift that occurred on May 17th, 2028. It was triggered by intensified underwater anomalous activity by undocumented sources, resulting in widespread devastation across Level 335, causing a significant portion of the populated landmass to be underwater, hundreds dead or missing, and thousands displaced. This event is widely known as the Wake's deadliest natural disaster ever recorded, heavily defying standard atmospheric and meteorological physics. Sudden thermal displacement from multiple locations caused a dramatic increase in water temperature, forming entire hurricanes in just a 72-hour timespan. The land shifted so violently that the surrounding air was pulled down, creating a vacuum and intensifying the vortex.

Constant earthquakes caused the islands to sink significantly further into the ocean and fracture. A notable case is Berry Island, inhabited by almost 280 people, which was torn in half, killing many and forcing the population to retreat to Bernhart Island, where most refugees reside as of now. However, the tunnel systems weren't safe either, as multiple sections had to be sealed off due to structural failures to prevent water from flooding additional areas and sinking the archipelagos even more. Anchoria received very limited international aid at the time, as the transfer of logistics proved impossible due to safety hazards and the destruction or severance of many important logistical hubs.

The Anchorian Department of Public Safety swiftly enforced evacuation procedures. Multiple islands and tunnel sections were quickly evacuated, sometimes too hurriedly, as structural containment protocols ultimately required the sealing of multiple tunnel sections before all civilians managed to evacuate safely. The sealing of these tunnels remains a controversial topic, especially in the City of Piscor, where the population was not adequately warned, leading to many people trampling each other during the evacuation and leaving some 36 people behind.

This event has permanently changed Level 335's landscape and biosphere, with many islands either submerged or rendered uninhabitable. Geological phenomena have affected many breeding grounds of rare, exotic marine life, which could lead to endangerment or extinction in the near future. Furthermore, the damage to the tunnel systems caused thousands to be displaced, and transportation became limited. The population has become centralized, with the Island of Bernhart containing almost 98% of the current population. The event also negatively impacted the living standards in the State of Anchoria because of this centralization. As of now, it is recorded that Anchoria has lost some 1,240,000 Stern in damages. International and humanitarian aid for Anchoria is gradually rising in light of the recent events.
