I stare at the note. Why? I never had any use to them. They didn’t know who I was. And they didn’t owe me anything. And I didn’t know who they were either. So why do they even bother?

I’m still uncertain and skeptical, as I should be. 

But maybe, just maybe, there was something to like about them, at the very least.




The Wake is not a cold dead place.

